docs {
  ## PUT /api/users/{id}
  
  **Description**  
  Updates user information for the specified user ID.  
  Allowed for admins or the user themselves, if the email is verified.
  
  ---
  
  ### Request
  
  - **Method:** `PUT`
  - **Endpoint:** `/api/users/{id}`
  - **Authentication:** Required (`accessToken` cookie)
  - **Authorization:**
    - Admins (`role_id = 1`) may update any user
    - Users may update their own account only
    - Email verification is required in both cases
  
  ---
  
  ### Path parameters
  
  | Parameter | Type   | Required | Description            |
  |-----------|--------|----------|------------------------|
  | `id`      | number | Yes      | ID of the user to update |
  
  ---
  
  ### Request body
  
  At least one of the following fields must be provided:
  
  ```json
  {
    "first_name": "Luna",
    "last_name": "Pixel",
    "email": "luna@example.com",
    "password": "newpassword123"
  }
  ```
  
  ---
  
  ### Successful response
  
  | Status | Description           |
  |--------|-----------------------|
  | 200    | User updated successfully |
  
  ```json
  {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
      "id": 7,
      "email": "luna@example.com",
      "first_name": "Luna",
      "last_name": "Pixel",
      "role_id": 3,
      "verified": true
    }
  }
  ```
  
  ---
  
  ### Error responses
  
  | Status | Message                         | Condition                                |
  |--------|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
  | 400    | `At least one field required`   | Empty or invalid request body            |
  | 401    | `Authentication required`       | No token present                         |
  | 401    | `Invalid or expired token`      | Token malformed or expired               |
  | 403    | `Access denied`                 | Not admin and not updating own account   |
  | 403    | `Email not verified`            | Authenticated user has not verified email |
  | 404    | `User not found`                | No user exists with the specified ID     |
  | 500    | `Error updating user`           | Unexpected server/database error         |
  
  ---
  
  ### Notes
  
  - You can partially update user data; only provided fields will be changed.
  - Role changes must be handled via the dedicated admin route (`PUT /api/users/admin/{id}`).
  
}
